{
  "info": {
    "name": "Library Management API",
    "_postman_id": "library-api-collection-v1",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for the Library Management API teaching project.\n\n## Setup\n1. Create a Postman Environment with variables:\n   - `base_url`: http://localhost:8000\n   - `access_token`: (auto-filled by Login request)\n   - `refresh_token`: (auto-filled by Login request)\n\n2. Run the **Register** and **Login** requests first.\n3. The Login request auto-saves tokens to environment variables.\n4. All subsequent authenticated requests use `{{access_token}}` automatically.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "access_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "refresh_token", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "description": "User registration, login (JWT token acquisition), token refresh, and logout.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register", ""] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"testmember\",\n  \"email\": \"testmember@example.com\",\n  \"first_name\": \"Test\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Member\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePass123!\",\n  \"password_confirm\": \"SecurePass123!\",\n  \"role\": \"member\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Register a new library member account. No authentication required."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201 Created', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has user object', function() {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('user');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.user).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.user).to.have.property('username');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.eql('User registered successfully.');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (Get Tokens)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login", ""] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"testmember\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePass123!\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Login with credentials to receive JWT access and refresh tokens.\n\nThe test script automatically saves tokens to environment variables:\n- `access_token` — used in Authorization header for all authenticated requests\n- `refresh_token` — used to get new access tokens when they expire"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains access and refresh tokens', function() {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('access');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('refresh');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Auto-save tokens to environment variables",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('access_token', json.access);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('refresh_token', json.refresh);",
                  "    console.log('Tokens saved to environment variables.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/refresh/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "refresh", ""] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Use the refresh token to obtain a new access token.\n\nAccess tokens expire after 15 minutes (configured in SIMPLE_JWT settings).\nWhen you get a 401 error, use this endpoint to refresh.\n\nWith ROTATE_REFRESH_TOKENS=True, a new refresh token is also returned."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Save the new tokens",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('access_token', json.access);",
                  "    console.log('Access token refreshed.');",
                  "}",
                  "if (json.refresh) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('refresh_token', json.refresh);",
                  "    console.log('Refresh token rotated.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout (Blacklist Token)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/logout/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "logout", ""] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Logout by blacklisting the refresh token.\n\nAfter this, the refresh token cannot be used to get new access tokens.\nThe current access token remains valid until it expires (15 min)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Clear saved tokens after logout",
                  "pm.environment.set('access_token', '');",
                  "pm.environment.set('refresh_token', '');",
                  "console.log('Tokens cleared from environment.');"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get My Profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/profile/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "profile", ""] },
            "description": "Get the current user's profile. Requires authentication."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Profile has required fields', function() {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('username');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('email');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('role');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Change Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/change-password/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "change-password", ""] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"old_password\": \"SecurePass123!\",\n  \"new_password\": \"NewSecurePass456!\",\n  \"new_password_confirm\": \"NewSecurePass456!\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Change the current user's password. Requires old password verification."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Books",
      "description": "Book catalog operations. List and retrieve are public; create/update/delete require librarian or admin role.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Books",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/books/?page=1&page_size=10",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "books", ""],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
                { "key": "page_size", "value": "10" },
                { "key": "search", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "category", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "author", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "available", "value": "true", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "ordering", "value": "-created_at", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "published_after", "value": "2020-01-01", "disabled": true }
              ]
            },
            "description": "List all books with pagination. Public endpoint — no authentication required.\n\nAvailable query parameters:\n- `search`: Search in title, author name, ISBN\n- `category`: Filter by category ID\n- `author`: Filter by author ID\n- `available`: true/false — filter by availability\n- `ordering`: Field to sort by. Prefix with `-` for descending\n- `published_after` / `published_before`: Date range filter"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK', function() {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Response is paginated', function() {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('count');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('results');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.results).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Book Detail",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/books/1/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "books", "1", ""] },
            "description": "Get detailed information for a specific book by ID."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200 OK or 404 if not found', function() {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 404]);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    pm.test('Book has required fields', function() {",
                  "        const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "        pm.expect(json).to.have.property('title');",
                  "        pm.expect(json).to.have.property('author');",
                  "        pm.expect(json).to.have.property('is_available');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Book (Auth Required)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/books/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "books", ""] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"The Pragmatic Programmer\",\n  \"author\": 1,\n  \"category\": 1,\n  \"isbn\": \"9780135957059\",\n  \"description\": \"A classic guide for developers on software craftsmanship.\",\n  \"published_date\": \"2019-09-13\",\n  \"available_copies\": 3,\n  \"total_copies\": 3\n}"
            },
            "description": "Create a new book. Requires librarian or admin role.\n\nNote: `author` and `category` are IDs, not nested objects."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201 Created or 403 if not authorized', function() {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([201, 403]);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Book",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/books/1/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "books", "1", ""] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"description\": \"Updated description for this book.\",\n  \"available_copies\": 5,\n  \"total_copies\": 5\n}"
            },
            "description": "Partially update a book. Requires librarian or admin role.\n\nUse PATCH for partial updates (only include fields you want to change).\nUse PUT for full replacement (all fields required)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Book",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/books/1/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "books", "1", ""] },
            "description": "Delete a book. Requires librarian or admin role."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Check Book Availability",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/books/1/availability/", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "books", "1", "availability", ""] },
            "description": "Check availability status for a specific book.\n\nThis is a custom action on the BookViewSet.\nReturns: is_available, available_copies, total_copies, borrowed_copies."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    pm.test('Availability response has required fields', function() {",
                  "        const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "        pm.expect(json).to.have.property('is_available');",
                  "        pm.expect(json).to.have.property('available_copies');",
                  "        pm.expect(json).to.have.property('total_copies');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Authors & Categories",
